FBIS4-32105 "dreeu119_i_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-119 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA `Abdic's Forces' Continue Artillery `Abdic's Forces' Continue Artillery Attacks AU2006144694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 20 Jun 94 AU2006144694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] [Text] Abdic's forces have continued to use long-range artillery from well inside the occupied territory of Velika Kladusa, with continuing support by the chetniks from the so-called Serbian autonomous region of Krajina. The intensity of the shelling with tanks, howitzers, and mortars is best illustrated by the fact that over the last two days from [words indistinct] they have fired over 6,000 shells, razing [word indistinct] villages to the ground. There have been many casualties. Since midday, the members of the Kladusa paramilitary have intensified their attacks along the entire front line, and reliable reports claim that Abdic's (?fascist) headquarters is preparing a new offensive and new attacks to recapture lost ground. However, he still has problems with forceful mobilization, and with generally mobilization, since the population is simply rejecting all calls. It is important to stress that the population's cooperation is [word indistinct] every day.
